- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses an acoustic model to extract phonetic information, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques such as CNNs, DNNs, and HMMs to solve the audio-to-score matching problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper extensively uses machine learning techniques to solve the problem.
